  "text": "Alcian blue staining was performed according to the method described by De Bari et al. [CITATION_1] . Matrices and pellets were washed with PBS, fixed with methanol for 30 minutes at -20°C, washed with Milli-Q water, and covered with 0.5 % Alcian blue 8 GS (Chroma) in 1M HCl. After overnight staining, cultures were washed extensively with Milli Q-water and extracted with 0.2 ml of 6 M guanidine HCl in Milli-Q water for 6 h at room temperature. The optical density of the extracted dye was measured at 650 nm using an ELISA reader MRX (Dynatech Laboratories). Adipose tissue-derived MSC from four different donors were used and four samples were prepared per donor and carrier material. Data were evaluated by Mann-Whitney-U test.",
